io.advantageous.qbit.queue

Interface ReceiveQueueListener<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Input
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ServiceMethodHandler
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    NoOpInputMethodCallQueueListener

    public interface ReceiveQueueListener<T>
extends Input
    Created by Richard on 7/18/14. Simplifies queue handler loop code by abstracting queue operations.

    The nitty gritty of polling the queue which can vary from one implementation to another is abstracted These are all callback method to notify you when the queue has an item, when the queue is empty, etc.

      • empty

        default void empty()
        Notifies the queue listener that currently the queue is empty. This is good for batch operations. This could mean the queue is empty or we reached our max batch size limit.

      • limit

        default void limit()
        Notifies the queue listener that we processed up to batch size. This is good for batch operations. This could mean the queue is empty or we reached our max batch size limit.

      • shutdown

        default void shutdown()
        Notifies the queue listener that currently the queue is closed for business.

      • idle

        default void idle()
        This means we did not find an item. We waited for an item as well and there was still not an item in the queue This would be a good time to do some clean up.
